w York | publisher=Warner | isbn=0-446-85553-7}}\n* {{cite book | author=Kazan, Elia | title=The Anatolian | year=1982 | location=New York | publisher=Knopf | isbn=0-394-52560-4 | url=https://archive.org/details/anatolian00kaza }}\n* {{cite book | author=Kazan, Elia | title=Elia Kazan: A Life | publisher=Knopf | year=1988 | location=New York | isbn=0-394-55953-3 | url=https://archive.org/details/eliakazanlife00kaza_0 }}\n* {{cite book | author=Kazan, Elia | title=Beyond the Aegean | year=1994 | location=New York | publisher=Knopf | isbn=0-679-42565-9 | url=https://archive.org/details/beyondaegean00kaza }}\n* {{cite book | author=Kazan, Elia | author2=Young, Jeff | title=The Master Director Discusses His Films | publisher=Newmarket Press | year=1999 | location=New York | isbn=1-55704-338-8 | url=https://archive.org/details/kazanmasterdirec00kaza }}\n* {{cite book | author=Schickel, Richard | title=Elia Kazan | year=2005 | location=New York | publisher=Harper Collins | isbn=978-0-06-019579-3}}\n* {{cite book | author=Kazan, Elia | title=Kazan on Directing | year=2009 | location=New York | publisher=Knopf | isbn=978-0-307-26477-0 | url=https://archive.org/details/kazanondirecting00kaza }}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Biography}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book | author=Jones, David, Richard | title=Great directors at work : Stanislavsky, Brecht, Kazan, Brook  | year=1986 | location=Berkeley ; London  | publisher=University of California Press | isbn=0-520-04601-3}}\n* {{cite book | author=Ciment, Michel | title=An American Odyssey  | year=1988| location=London  | publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing Ltd. | isbn=0-7475-0241-2}}\n* {{cite book | author=Schickel, Richard| title=Elia Kazan: A Biography | publisher=HarperCollins Publishers | year=2005 | location=New York | isbn=0-06-019579-7}}\n* {{cite book | author=Murphy, Brenda | title=Tennessee Williams and Elia Kazan : a collaboration in the theatre | year=2006 | location= Cambridge| pub